mkdir   -- Create the DIRECTORY(ies), if they do not already exist.

syntax:

mkdir [OPTION]... DIRECTORY...


::

mkdir linux         -- this creates a directory names linux

mkdir linux is fun  -- this create 3 diretory named linux is fun

mkdir ../           -- create directory in parent directory

mkdir -v linux      -- verbose it shows whats has been done

mkdir -p            -- creates other directory 

example : mkdir -p 1/2/3/  this creates directory 1 which have 2 inside and 2 have 3 inside

